page.title: 01QUEENBOROUGH - a summary
page.content: The river and tidal mud flats in our area are under the jurisdiction of Medway Ports Authority. The rural marshes of Chetney and Sheppey are used mainly for animal grazing. {Queenborough,}with a population of 6000, is a large industrial village. There are some small new developments but much of its terraced housing is pre-1914. Some of the houses are much older and steeped in naval history. The church dates from the 14thC. The large, mainly council, estate of{Rushenden}has its own parade of shops and community centre. The old village of{Westminster}has been demolished and is now a lorry park and imported car holding yard.
